.TH "snd_hdac_calc_stream_format" 9 "snd_hdac_calc_stream_format" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_calc_stream_format \- calculate the format bitset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" snd_hdac_calc_stream_format
.BI "(unsigned int rate "  ","
.BI "unsigned int channels "  ","
.BI "snd_pcm_format_t format "  ","
.BI "unsigned int maxbps "  ","
.BI "unsigned short spdif_ctls "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rate" 12
the sample rate
.IP "channels" 12
the number of channels
.IP "format" 12
the PCM format (SNDRV_PCM_FORMAT_XXX)
.IP "maxbps" 12
the max. bps
.IP "spdif_ctls" 12
HD-audio SPDIF status bits (0 if irrelevant)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calculate the format bitset from the given rate, channels and th PCM format.

Return zero if invalid.
